course_metadata.title: Digital twins in real estate management

content_chunks.content: This course explores the field of real estate management (REM). It will examine the basic principles of REM to understand techniques and strategies to tackle with profitability and operational issues. The course is designed for anyone wishing to understand and/or study and of develop the essential concepts needed for real estate, surveying, land management, housing, property, planning and construction. Focused on the best practices and emerging trends in the global and European RE industry, this course helps you expand your RE expertise and strengthen your strategic decision-making capabilities. When introducing digital tools in real estate business, digital twin is a digital replica of any physical object, system, or process, contextualized in a digital version of its environment. Digital twins can help many kinds of organizations – incl. REM companies – to simulate real situations and their outcomes, ultimately allowing them to make better decisions. Possibilities of using digital twins for RE industry are discussed during the course.

Digital twins for real estate management, property simulation, and asset portfolio optimization - this course delivers practical skills in applying digital twin technology for strategic real estate decision-making. Master Building Information Modeling (BIM) for property asset management, implement digital tools for maintenance management principles, and develop real estate business simulation models for profitability analysis. Learn property vs asset vs portfolio management strategies, apply land management and ownership frameworks, and utilize building maintenance types for operational efficiency. Gain expertise in digital twin technology for physical asset mirroring, implement digital tools for real estate service models, and create strategic approaches to real estate management using contemporary digital solutions.

content_chunks.title: Different facets of real estate management – property vs asset vs portfolio vs facilities management
Historical background for real estate management and objectives of it in residential and in commercial sectors
Strategic approach to real estate management
Maintenance as an inevitable component of real estate management
Types of maintenance for built environment
Digital twin as a contemporary tool for mirroring the physical assets
Digital tools for RE management in service, e.g. service model
Examples of digitalised real estate management tools

courses_covered: Property vs asset vs portfolio management
